W3C Web Application Formats Working Group

comment:
Disregard the IANA registration and consider
WHATWG as authoritative instead of RFC 6454,
given that implementors (Web browsers)
care about the former, and the two differ greatly.

cite_title: W3C Web Application Formats Working Group

comment:
Any common "X-" prefixed headers should be included here,
even if there are no citations for them.
This is necessary for notice 1277 to work properly.
Many of these are taken from Wikipedia:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_header_fields
